He left Pyongyang in July saying progress had been made, but, a few hours later, North Korea denounced his "demands were those of a mobster."
At a meeting with Moon this month, North Korea pledged to dismantle a missile site and a nuclear complex if the U.S. enforces “corresponding measures.”
